<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<body class="page page--<%= pageClass %>">
<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<main id="main" class="main">

  <section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Security</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Security posture</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__lead">Plain-language overview of how we approach risk, access, and infrastructure.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--legal">
    <div class="container narrow legal-stack">
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>What this means</h2><p>We reduce attack surface by keeping systems understandable, limiting external dependencies, and preferring architectures that do not require blind trust.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Access</h2><p>Administrative access follows least privilege. Privileged actions are limited, reviewed, and treated as sensitive operations—not background noise.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Encryption</h2><p>We use modern encryption for data in transit and at rest where those controls apply. Design choices favor fewer data copies over convenience.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Infrastructure</h2><p>External services are added deliberately. Each integration is a liability budget line, not a feature checkbox.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>People and process</h2><p>Most failures start with humans. Operational discipline and verification steps are part of the security model, not an afterthought.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Reporting</h2><p>A coordinated disclosure channel will be published for production services. Until then, this section stays intentionally minimal.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/mobile-nav') %>
<script type="module" src="/src/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
